other_tests.findings: There is a hypodense lesion in segment 6 of the liver with peripheral nodular enhancement, likely hemangioma measuring 1.8 x 1.3 cm. The appendix is dilated, measuring up to 1.5 cm in diameter, with internal hyperdensities, likely appendicolith(s). Periappendiceal fat stranding and a small amount of fluid is seen tracking along the fascia. No extraluminal gas or drainable fluid collection is seen. No bowel obstruction is seen.
